<TITLE> India govt cuts excise duty, service tax rates </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Tue Feb 24, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The India government on Tuesday cut factory gate duties further and lowered service tax rates by 2 percent as it moved to protect the economy from the impact of the global economic crisis. Finance Minister Pranab Mukherjee in his reply to a debate on the 2009/10 federal budget cut excise duty across the board to 8 percent from 10 percent, and reduced the service tax rate to 10 percent from 12 percent on all taxable services. Mukherjee also said excise duty cuts of 4 percent unveiled earlier as part of a government stimulus package would be extended into the new fiscal year. He also reduced the excise duty on bulk cement to 8 percent and extended the customs cut on naphtha beyond March 31, 2009
